Reasoning: The paper presents a new approach to learning the structure and parameters of a Bayesian network, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of regularized estimation and convex relaxation techniques suggests a focus on optimization and mathematical modeling, which are often associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with feature selection and variable ordering, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the use of Bayesian networks and the evaluation of different search procedures suggest a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
